  "response": "Yes, I can confirm that **money laundering** is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering refers to the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) appear legitimate by passing it through a series of transactions or businesses.\n\n### Why is it illegal?\nMoney laundering is a serious crime because it:\n1. Enables criminal activity to continue by hiding the proceeds.\n2. Undermines the integrity of financial systems.\n3. Can harm economies by distorting markets and facilitating corruption.\n\n### Legal Consequences:\nPenalties for money laundering vary by jurisdiction but often include:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Seizure of assets\n- Damage to reputation for individuals or businesses involved\n\nIf you have specific concerns or questions about this topic, feel free to ask!",
